abstract: A total of 7.3 million people tuned in for "The Walking Dead" on Sunday night, including 4.8 million from age 18 to 49, making the episode the highest-rated drama episode ever on cable in that category.
snippet: A total of 7.3 million people tuned in for "The Walking Dead" on Sunday night, including 4.8 million from age 18 to 49, making the episode the highest-rated drama episode ever on cable in that category.
lead_paragraph: Hart Hanson, the creator of Fox's "Bones," may have said it best when the ratings for Sunday's second season premiere of AMC's "The Walking Dead" were released on Monday afternoon. "Wow," he wrote on Twitter. "Them zombies are coming for all of us on network TV."

headline.main: AMC Sets Record With 'The Walking Dead'
